  <span id="freeText8664177450388964190" style="display:none"><b>
  <i>"I gave you the best of me, and after you left, nothing was ever the same."</i>
</b><br /><br />Nicholas Sparks did it again. I think he secretly (not so secret anymore) enjoys RIPPING our hearts out. I cried. Not ashamed. 🤚🏼<br /><br />It started off as the mother of all clichés (not complaining), I still liked this a lot despite the very predictable, yet engaging plot; but I admit that some parts SHOOK me (not spoiling anything, you're gonna have to read this).<br />I'm glad I never gave up on Sparks and still am reading his beautiful novels (I do have a thing for typical romance).<br /><br />PS: I think I'm more in love with Tuck than anyone else in the book + I loved the movie WAY more since it added more action and characters ( - Bobby Cole, Dawson's cousin AND best friend - and he didn't even exist in the book) that, too, BROKE my heart even more and made my cry like a baby.</span>
